{{hstr|5774}}
עוּף / ‛ûph / oof
=== Etymology ===

A primitive root; 
=== Verb ===
to [[cover]] (with wings or obscurity); hence (as denominative from {{HH|5775}}) to [[fly]]; also (by implication of dimness) to faint (from the darkness of swooning): - brandish, be (wax) faint, flee away, fly (away - ), X set, shine forth, weary.